4.) Create three users (sysadmin1, sysadmin2, and sysadmin3) with their home directories without assigning passwords or using sudo. Create a supplementary group named rootgroup with a GID of 5001.
Add all three users to the rootgroup.

useradd -m sysadmin1
useradd -m sysadmin2
useradd -m sysadmin3

groupadd -g 5001 rootgroup

usermod -aG rootgroup sysadmin1
usermod -aG rootgroup sysadmin2
usermod -aG rootgroup sysadmin3

